==Usage== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:16-->
# Select one or more objects.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Part → Create a copy → [[Image:Part_RefineShape.svg|16px]] Refine shape}} option from the menu.
# For each object a cleaned, parametric copy is created
# The original objects are hidden.

== Notes == <!--T:6-->

<!--T:22-->
* Many [[Part_Workbench|Part]] objects and [[PartDesign_Workbench|PartDesign]] features have a {{PropertyData|Refine}} property. Setting that property to {{TRUE}} is preferable over using this command as it avoids an extra object.
* By default this command creates [[Glossary#Parametric|parametric]] copies. There is a [[Fine-tuning|fine-tuning]] parameter to change this to [[Glossary#Non-parametric|non-parametric]] copies.
* This command can be used after [[Part_ShapeFromMesh|converting a mesh to a shape]].
* Refining an object may prevent 3D printers from printing unwanted edges once the object is exported to a mesh format.
* Some interesting information about what is happening with placement and how to access by Python can be found in this [https://forum.freecad.org/viewtopic.php?t=77568#p675456 forum post].

